# Code Quality Standards

## TypeScript
- Use proper types for all variables
- Avoid `any` type - use specific interfaces
- Implement proper error handling
- Use strict mode

## React Best Practices
- Use functional components with hooks
- Implement proper cleanup in useEffect
- Avoid unnecessary re-renders
- Use refs for DOM manipulation
- Handle component mounting/unmounting properly

## Three.js Best Practices
- Dispose of geometries, materials, and renderers
- Handle window resize events
- Implement proper camera constraints
- Use efficient rendering loops
- Use dynamic imports with `{ ssr: false }` for Three.js

## General Code Standards
- Write clean, readable code
- Use meaningful variable names
- Comment complex logic
- Follow consistent formatting
- Test functionality before committing
